course_title: Selected Topics in Music - ORAL COMPOSITION

sections.comments: With 530C.  An analysis-and-practice class, students will invent short compositions incorporating rhythm techniques found in a variety of world traditions, and teach them to one another orally.   Please contact instructor for permission to register.

description: See School of Music schedule for description and prerequisites. Restricted to B. Mus. and B.A. in Music students.
